%div(class="page-content no-banner")
	%div(class="t")
		%div(class="plugins_sidebar")
			-if @page and @page.metadata('Bundle') and not @page.flagged_as?('bundle')
				%p
					This plugin (#{@page.heading}) is part of the 
					%a{href:@page.bundle.abspath}
						= @page.bundle.heading
				%p
					~ @page.bundle.metadata('Cost')
					
			:markdown
				### Where is the plugins section?
				The `<plugins>` section is located in Web.config, and is nested inside the `<resizer>` element, which is nested inside `<configuration>`. For examples, see [this sample Web.config file](/docs/configuration).
				### What is NuGet? 
				NuGet is a better way to manage your project's libraries, and is [fully supported by the ImageResizer](/docs/nuget).  
			-bundles.each do |bundle|
				%h3
					%a(href="#{bundle.abspath}")= bundle.heading
				%ul
					-bundle.bundle_plugins.each do |plugin|
						%li
							%a(href="#{plugin.abspath}")= plugin.heading
			%p
				Don't see the feature or plugin you're looking for? I do 
				%a(href='/plugins/custom')
					custom plugin development at 40% off my regular rates.
			
		
		-if @page and @page.lib("plusone")
			<div style="width:70px;padding-top:25px;float:right"><div class="g-plusone"></div></div>
		~ @page.to_html(self)
		-if @page and @page.lib("plusone")
			<div class="g-plusone"></div>
		%div(style="clear:both;")
	= haml :comments, :layout => false